                            <comment id="181906" author="pjones" created="Tue, 24 Jan 2017 14:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.10&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="181864" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 24 Jan 2017 05:25:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg Drokin (oleg.drokin@intel.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/24768/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/24768/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8932&quot; title=&quot;define a new network driver for ptl4lnd&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8932&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8932&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: define new network driver ptl4lnd&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: c54bf3faa29f576ceb47aa09531cd1456c450994&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="180094" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 9 Jan 2017 17:46:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also be aware that the time api lustre uses is being replaced by standard kernel functions and soon the typedefs in the LNet layer will be removed. Please make sure your drivers doesn&apos;t use typedefs and the lustre timer wrappers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="180088" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 9 Jan 2017 17:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gr&#233;goire Pichon (gregoire.pichon@bull.net) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/24768&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/24768&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8932&quot; title=&quot;define a new network driver for ptl4lnd&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8932&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8932&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: define new network driver ptl4lnd&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: b760d42ab45d52475b068d6a178c24e2748eee0d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="180079" author="pichong" created="Mon, 9 Jan 2017 16:57:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas,&lt;br/&gt;
The ptl4lnd is going to implement a LND based on the Portals 4 API, and is intended to be compatible with any hardware that supports this interface.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the notification about the LNet Multi-Rail project. I will have a look at the code and try to detect potential conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="177675" author="adilger" created="Wed, 14 Dec 2016 01:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gregoire, is this ptl4lnd based directly on the Portals API (i.e. it would be portable to other LNDs that implement the Portals 4 API), or would this be better named bxilnd?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that there is also work being done for LNet Multi-Rail in the &lt;tt&gt;multi-rail&lt;/tt&gt; branch of &lt;tt&gt;fs/lustre-release&lt;/tt&gt; that is planned to land for Lustre 2.10.  It would be worthwhile to look at the code in that branch to see what potential conflicts exist, and what needs to be done with the new LND to integrate with that change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
